# CODEOWNERS for contract-toaster
#
# Lines are evaluated bottom-up. The last matching pattern takes precedence.
# Owners listed here are required reviewers on pull requests touching the
# matching paths.
#
# Replace @exos-legal/gc and @exos-legal/engineering with actual GitHub
# handles or team slugs once the org is configured.
#
# NOTE — branch protection enforcement (issue #10 AC #3, deferred to Phase 0 #1):
#   The "Require review from Code Owners" branch protection setting is tracked
#   in Phase 0 issue #1 (repo bootstrap).  Enabling it requires GitHub Pro for
#   private repos and real team handles (not the placeholder slugs above).
#   CODEOWNERS path coverage is complete (this file); the branch-protection
#   enforcement layer is deferred to issue #1 pending org/billing readiness.

# Default — engineering reviews anything not otherwise specified
*                                       @exos-legal/engineering

# Legal-owned content. Any change to the playbook, schema, prompt overlay,
# model policy, standard form, corpus-governance contract, evaluation gate,
# or architecture issue register requires GC approval. Engineering co-reviews
# for technical correctness.
/playbooks/                             @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/prompts/                               @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/model-policy/                          @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/standard-forms/                        @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/docs/evaluation.md                     @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/docs/data-handling.md                  @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/docs/threat-model.md                   @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/docs/design-notes.md                   @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/docs/architecture-issue-spotting-*.md  @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/docs/playbook-governance.md            @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/docs/output-contract.md                @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/docs/audit-queries.md                  @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/tests/gold-fixtures/                   @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering

# Gold fixtures — legal review required for any fixture with provenance=production
# (de-identification sign-off must be present; see docs/evaluation.md § De-identification standard)
/tests/gold-fixtures/                   @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering

# Evaluation harness — GC sign-off required before any eval fixture or gate
# change can merge (architecture-review reconciliation #10, issue #49).
# eval/ is a future directory; the rule is pre-registered so no content can
# land there without GC approval.
/eval/**                                @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering

# Architecture and runbook changes — both
/ARCHITECTURE.md                        @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/RUNBOOK.md                             @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering

# Licence and confidentiality posture — GC only
/LICENSE                                @exos-legal/gc

# Infrastructure that affects data residency, encryption, or access
# control — both should sign off
/infra/lib/data-stack.ts                @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
/infra/lib/auth-stack.ts                @exos-legal/gc @exos-legal/engineering
